n\n----\n\nFormed in 1967, Blue Öyster Cult, the Long Island (NY) based band is revered within the hard rock scene for its pioneering work. Eric Bloom, Donald Roeser a.k.a. Buck Dharma, Allen Lanier, Joe Bouchard and Albert Bouchard record their first self-titled album in 1972.\n \nThanks to inspirations like Black Sabbath, The Stooges and many others, BÖC quickly became famous worldwide, with hits like \"(Do not Fear) The Reaper\" (1976) - played in several horror films - and others classics such as \"Godzilla\" (1977) and \"Burnin’ for You\" (1981).\n \nThe band is often cited as a major influence by other acts such as Metallica.\nThe current line-up consists of Eric Bloom (vocals - guitar - keyboards), Buck Dharma (vocals - guitar), Richie Castellano (guitar - keyboards), Jules Radino (drums) and Danny Miranda (bass).\n \nAfter a noteworthy performance at the Hellfest festival in 2017, Blue Öyster Cult will be back at the Trianon on the 2nd of June 2020, for a unique show in France!','https://la-scene-parisienne.s3.eu-west-3.amazonaws.com/covers/2020/blue-oyster-cult-paris-le-trianon.jpg',0,0,NULL,'{\"rsvp\": {\"maybe\": 3880, \"invited\": null, \"noreply\": 137, \"declined\": 0, \"attending\": 446}, \"cover\": \"https://scontent-ams4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/s720x720/76652820_3005703822791934_4895631425966964736_o.jpg?_nc_cat=109&_nc_sid=b386c4&_nc_ohc=DZNdiIOejHoAX-MI9gs&_nc_ht=scontent-ams4-1.xx&_nc_tp=7&oh=98ced15a291079285b994b85018ea55d&oe=5EBFC549\", \"local_cover\": \"/2020/blue-oyster-cult-paris-le-trianon.jpg\"}','6fb14073-cf03-4da2-b7b7-5ebff9cb5730','2530456157229803','{\"meta\": {\"rsvp\": {\"maybe\": 3887, \"invited\": null, \"noreply\": 137, \"declined\": 0, \"attending\": 447}, \"cover\": \"https://scontent-ams4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/s720x720/76652820_3005703822791934_4895631425966964736_o.jpg?_nc_cat=109&_nc_sid=b386c4&_nc_ohc=wUUQXjMg7v4AX_PyTaX&_nc_ht=scontent-ams4-1.xx&_nc_tp=7&oh=4864ef9dfda5fc34403825f2b46584f3&oe=5EB3E7C9\"}, \"name\": \"B